args: The Shadewolves are truly down\nto a single man now.
Robelle fought and killed for revenge,\nand so lost his way.
A directive from our homeland?\nThis must be ill news indeed if\nyou ran so to deliver it to me.
Hm? Rare for you to hurry me.\n...This is an order to return!
＂We have readied a post that will make\nuse of your abundant combat experience.＂
Mmm.\nDoesn't sound like a bad assignment.
Y-you tore up your orders again!
I'm not going back. I can't.
I abandoned everything in the name of\nrevenge—including my home and duty—\nyet now that revenge feels hopeless.
Though I have lost everything,\nthere is yet something ahead for me.
...Here. Give this blade and this sword to\nyour superior and tell them I died in my\nblind pursuit of vengeance.
Then never return to this land again.
(Farewell, Robelle. I will never forget\nthe lessons you taught me.)
Thank you for your service to me, Noelle.\nThough you were but following orders,\nknow that I appreciate it.
I...I wasn't coming here because\nI was ordered to!
Forget all that has happened and be free.\nThat is what I intend to do, and you would\nbe wise to follow my example.
Commander, I will come back here.\nI'm a messenger and...and I connect\npeople with each other...
Ah, Victor. I'm sorry again\nabout what happened.
I wish to thank you again for\nagreeing to bury Robelle.
It was the least we could do.\nBut how are you faring?
I would like to say that all is well,\nbut in truth, I think I need some time.
I lived my life bent on revenge.\nI sacrificed everything for it.
But seeing Robelle made me realize\nthat I lacked resolve.
I claimed to live for revenge, and yet was\nunable to take the steps he did to claim it.
Oh, I know. His actions were abhorrent.\nBut they were also the only place that\nmy path could ever lead.
Robelle taught me what it truly means to\nlive for revenge, and I cannot become him.
Yes. For a while, I'd thought to seek a\npath that allowed the world to live in\npeace, but now...
I'll never move on if I don't atone for\nthe comrades who died so I might live.
But how will you do that?
In truth, I am not certain. But first,\nI intend to visit their homes.

I will see the sights they did.
Eat and drink what they consumed.
Feel the breezes that touched their skin.
I will do this and simply...think.
...Heh. They might not be happy that the\nman for whom they sacrificed their lives\nhas abandoned his dream of revenge.
I'm sure that's not the case.
A good thought, if nothing else.\nStill, it's a bit embarrassing to go on\na soul-searching journey at my age.
You seem much more at peace than\nwhen you first came here, Victor.
You've even started to laugh a little.
Heh. Perhaps so. If true, then all credit\ngoes to you and your merry band.
Nothing would make me happier than\nknowing we've been a positive influence.
And on that note, I think it is time\nthat I was off.
Thank you. And when you find yourself\nfighting the Empire, know that I will be\nat your side as any comrade would.
